  "texts": [
    "Finally, hybrid E/E architectures integrated with domain-oriented and zone-oriented characteristics are expected.",
    "State of the Art of E/E Architecture Topologies in Academia and IndustryThis section provides a comprehensive examination of the current state of E/E architecture topologies in both academic and industrial domains.In academia, Stolz et al. [28] from BOSCH pioneered the integration of functions from multiple ECUs into DCUs, addressing the burgeoning complexity in E/E architecture topologies.",
    "Navale et al. [9] from BOSCH firstly introduced a roadmap of the development of E/E architecture topologies with six main stages, including modular, integration, centralization, fusion, vehicle computer, and vehicle cloud computing stage.",
    "And they discussed how to attempt to make a paradigm shift in terms of networks, safety, and security, etc.",
